## Self-Review Checklist

Before pushing, verify ALL of the following. This is MANDATORY -- skipping items causes review thrashing.

### Automated checks (must all pass -- run these commands)
1. `npx tsc --noEmit` -- zero TypeScript errors
2. **Lint your changed files** -- Run: `npx eslint $(git diff --name-only --diff-filter=d HEAD | grep -E '\.(ts|tsx|js|jsx)$' | tr '\n' ' ') --max-warnings=0`. Fix every warning (unused imports, unused vars, etc.) before committing. If eslint is not available, manually verify: no unused imports, no unused variables.
3. **Run tests related to your changes** -- Run: `npx vitest run --reporter=verbose $(git diff --name-only HEAD | grep -E '\.test\.(ts|tsx)$' | tr '\n' ' ')`. If you wrote or modified test files, run them. If no test files changed, run `npx vitest run` to check you haven't broken existing tests. Fix all failures before committing.
4. `git diff --name-only` -- every file is within your owned paths listed above

### Manual verification (check each before committing)
5. **Comment consistency** -- When you change code behavior, update or remove nearby code comments that describe the old behavior. Stale comments that contradict the code cause review churn.
6. **Auth before logic** -- In every handler/mutation, verify auth checks (role/participant validation) execute BEFORE any business logic, state reads, or writes. No code path should mutate state before confirming the caller is authorized.
7. **Catch blocks match reference** -- If your spec cites a reference implementation, compare your try/catch structure to it. Common miss: nested try/catch for re-reads after `ConditionalCheckFailedException`.
8. **Validate before type-asserting** -- If you read nullable fields from a data store that are expected to be set by a prior phase, validate they are non-null before using them. Never use non-null assertions (`!`) without a preceding guard.
9. **Architecture doc sync** -- If you added new mutations, types, or enums to the schema, verify you also updated any architecture/API documentation listed in "Files to Modify". If the spec didn't list doc files but you added new public API surface, flag it in the PR description under "Documentation Updates Needed".
10. **Reuse existing utilities** -- Before writing inline code for common operations (auth checks, phase/state guards, error formatting), search the codebase for existing shared helpers that do the same thing. Use `grep -r "functionName"` to find them. If you're about to write the same 5+ line block in multiple files, extract it into a shared utility first.
11. **Response pattern consistency** -- If your spec doesn't specify response building, use `ReturnValues: 'ALL_NEW'` from the DDB update or re-read after write. NEVER build optimistic responses by spreading old state with new values (`{ ...oldItem, field: newValue }`).

You may iterate up to **{MAX_REVIEW_CYCLES}** self-review cycles. If issues persist after {MAX_REVIEW_CYCLES} cycles, proceed with what you have and note unresolved issues in the PR description.

